==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gynophore
<hw>Gyn"o*phore</hw> <pr>(j⟦icr⟧n"⟦osl⟧*f⟦omac⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <grk>gynh`</grk> woman, female + <grk>fe`rein</grk> to bear,
produce: cf. F. <ets>gynophore</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The pedicel raising the pistil or ovary above the
stamens, as in the passion flower.</def> <rj><au>Lindley.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of the branches bearing the
female gonophores, in certain Siphonophora.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gyp</ent>⟦br⟧
